[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer‐detected stack‐buffer‐overflow occurred during a libFuzzer run [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the Mongoose HTTP parser. The overflow is triggered in the formatted output[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_vxprintf` and its helpers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when handling malformed or unexpected [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput in `mg_http_parse`. Specifically, a one‐byte write overruns a small stack [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer in `mg_vxprintf`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The log clearly reports a stack‐buffer‐overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS: [0m[1;36m46[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_pfn_iobuf_private`, part of the Mongoose printf implementation. [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer identifies a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m‐byte write past the end of a local buffer on the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Invocation chain  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → `mg_http_parse` → `mg_log` → formatting routines [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`mg_vxprintf`, `mg_snprintf`, `mg_dtoa`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → `mg_pfn_iobuf_private`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Buffer details  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     In `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.[0m[1;92mc:247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, there are two automatic arrays:  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `tmp` spanning bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - `tmp371` spanning bytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     The overflow happens at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, immediately past `tmp371`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Sanitizer report  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     AddressSanitizer’s shadow‐memory dump shows `f1` and `f3` markers around the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow site, confirming a stack red zone violation.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability classification  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a classic stack‐buffer‐overflow defect in a string‐formatting routine. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMalicious or malformed input can trigger an out‐of‐bounds write on the stack.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Affected code areas for further investigation  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `src/mongoose/src/fmt.c`, especially the `mg_vxprintf` function and its helper [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`scpy` at fmt.[0m[1;92mc:233[0m[39m.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `src/mongoose/src/printf.c`, particularly `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_putchar_iobuf_static`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Callers of the formatting code, such as `mg_log` in `src/mongoose/src/log.c` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the HTTP parser entry point `mg_http_parse` in `src/mongoose/src/http.c`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions are made about the root cause or fix strategy; this report focuses [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the observed overflow, its context, and the code regions that merit a holistic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreview.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐Cause Identification[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack overflow stems from the `%e/%E` formatting branch in `mg_vxprintf` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/fmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A local buffer `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is passed as destination to `mg_dtoa` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[33mdstlen[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m`, allowing up to [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m characters plus a NUL write, which overruns the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte `tmp` buffer. Downstream, `scpy` reads up to `k` bytes from `tmp`, but the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreal overflow already occurred when writing into `tmp`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Preservation[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Preserve the existing formatting logic for `%e/%E`: computing exponent, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproducing mantissa via `mg_dtoa`, emitting literal `e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`E`, then printing exponent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdigits via `mg_lld`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter or remove `scpy` or other format specifiers. No changes to the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing harness or logging invocation.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Implementation Steps[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In src/fmt.c, locate the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch starting around line [0m[1;36m316[0m[39m in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Replace the small fixed buffer and hard‐coded length with a buffer sized to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccommodate the maximum possible `%e` output plus NUL, and pass its true size to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_dtoa`. For example:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      -    char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Buffer must hold [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m digit + [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m + width digits + NUL, so allocate at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleast width+[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +    char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[33m...[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      -    k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +    k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Leave the following steps unchanged:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `[0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; n++;`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `k = [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m After `mg_dtoa` and `mg_lld`, you may add an `[0m[1;35massert[0m[1;39m([0m[39mk < [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` to guard against future regressions in buffer usage.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By sizing `tmp` to at least `width + [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m` bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere [0m[33mwidth[0m[39m==[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m here, so [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtotal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and by passing `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as the destination length, we eliminate any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpossibility of `mg_dtoa` writing beyond the end of the local buffer.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of a hard‐coded constant ensures future changes to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp`’s size automatically stay in sync.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach localizes the change to one formatting branch and incurs [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegligible additional stack usage [0m[1;39m([0m[39m< [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. It preserves all existing [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatting features and the fuzzer entry points.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Slightly larger stack usage in the `%e` branch: negligible for typical server [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor embedded uses.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If downstream logic relied on the truncated [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte mantissa, output precision [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now be correct and compliant with the width parameter. Existing tests should [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly be more accurate; no behavior is removed.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adding an `assert` is safe in debug builds and helps catch future overshoots, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut can be omitted in production if assert‐free code is required.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild with AddressSanitizer and run the libFuzzer target; the prior [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack‐buffer‐overflow in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` should no longer be triggered.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing format‐string tests and HTTP‐parser tests to confirm no [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregressions.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Further Harness or Utility Changes[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All modifications are confined to the `%e/%E` branch in `mg_vxprintf`. The [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `mg_http_parse`, `mg_log`, and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_pfn_iobuf_private` remain untouched. This ensures compatibility with current [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests and fuzzing workflows.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes and passes the new size to `mg_dtoa`. However, [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond local buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the same function frame.[0m                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack trace shows a WRITE of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at an address within the stack [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mframe of `mg_vxprintf` in `src/fmt.c`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ `scpy` → `mg_vxprintf.specialized.[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m` → `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m247[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer’s summary indicates that two stack objects exist in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf` frame:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • ‘tmp’ at offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m681[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, t = mul; t >= [0m[1;36m1.0[0m[39m && s + n < [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m682[0m[39m:      int ch = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39md [0m[35m/[0m[39m t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m683[0m[39m:      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || ch > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch + [0m[32m'0'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m684[0m[39m:      d -= ch * t;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m685[0m[39m:      t [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10.0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m686[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m687[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" --> [0m[32m[[0m[32m%g[0m[32m][0m[32m -> %g %g [0m[32m([0m[32m%d[0m[32m)[0m[32m [0m[32m[[0m[32m%.*s[0m[32m][0m[32m\n"[0m[39m, saved, d, t, n, s + n, buf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m688[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m689[0m[39m:    while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mt >= [0m[1;36m1.0[0m[39m && n + s < [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mn++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m, t [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10.0[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m690[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms + n < [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mn + s++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m691[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m" 1--> [0m[32m[[0m[32m%g[0m[32m][0m[32m -> [0m[32m[[0m[32m%.*s[0m[32m][0m[32m\n"[0m[39m, saved, s + n, buf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m692[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!tz && n > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m targ_width = width + n;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m693[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, t = [0m[1;36m0.1[0m[39m; s + n < [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && n < targ_width; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m694[0m[39m:      int ch = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39md [0m[35m/[0m[39m t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m695[0m[39m:      buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch + [0m[32m'0'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m696[0m[39m:      d -= ch * t;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m697[0m[39m:      t [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10.0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m698[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m699[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m700[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m701[0m[39m:  while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtz && n > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'0'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m n--;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Trim trailing zeroes[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m702[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtz && n > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m n--;           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Trim trailing dot[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m703[0m[39m:  n += s;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m704[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m n = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m705[0m[39m:  buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mn[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m706[0m[39m:  return [0m[1;35mmg_snprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdst, dstlen, [0m[32m"%s"[0m[39m, buf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m707[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m708[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m709[0m[39m:static size_t [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *buf, int64_t val, bool is_signed, bool is_hex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m710[0m[39m:  const char *letters = [0m[32m"0123456789abcdef"[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m711[0m[39m:  uint64_t v = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m val;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m712[0m[39m:  size_t s = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, n, i;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m713[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_signed && val < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'-'[0m[39m, v = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m-val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m714[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m This loop prints a number in reverse order. I guess this is because we[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m715[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m write numbers from right to left: least significant digit comes last.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m716[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Maybe because we use Arabic numbers, and Arabs write RTL?[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m717[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_hex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m718[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; v; v >>= [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = letters[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mv & [0m[1;36m15[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m719[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m720[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; v; v [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = letters[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mv % [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m721[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m722[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Reverse a string[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m723[0m[39m:  for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < n [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m724[0m[39m:    char t = buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m725[0m[39m:    buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - i - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - i - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = t;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m726[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m727[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mval == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mn++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Handle special case[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m728[0m[39m:  return n + s;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m729[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m730[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer reports show that in `mg_vxprintf`’s `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch, a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond local buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m of only [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes is being overrun by the call to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_lld`, which writes an unbounded number of digits [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplus optional sign[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with no [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuilt-in length check.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The initial patch only enlarged the first buffer used by `mg_dtoa` from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m→[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes, but left the second [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte buffer untouched. Therefore the overflow simply [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmoved from the first to the second buffer.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Enlarge the second buffer in the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch to match the safe size used[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melsewhere in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring ample headroom for any [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent string [0m[1;39m([0m[39msign + up to ~[0m[1;36m3[0m[39m digits for normal IEEE double exponents[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Continue to pass the new buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m into `mg_dtoa` for the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmantissa, and rely on the larger buffer to absorb the exponent print in the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent `mg_lld` call.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Do not modify `mg_lld` itself [0m[1;39m([0m[39mavoiding invasive changes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, since enlarging [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer is sufficient to prevent overflow given realistic exponent ranges.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Do not alter any harness, fuzzing logic, or external tests. This patch only [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffects application code in `src/fmt.c`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Implementation Steps[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/fmt.c`, locate the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m318[0m[39m in the initial [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change the declaration[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update the `mg_dtoa` invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif not already[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to use `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength parameter. The subsequent `[0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call remains [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged, but now writes into a [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other changes are needed.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reference amalgamation in `mongoose.c` uses a [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m-byte buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for both mantissa and exponent formatting in its `%e` implementation. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMatching that proven pattern avoids overflow without altering core formatting [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By only enlarging the temporary buffer in the `%e` branch, existing behavior [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mprecision, padding, sign handling, exponent formatting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is preserved exactly.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack footprint increase is minimal and safe: [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes vs. previous [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external or harness code is touched, thus existing tests and fuzz harness [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain valid and unaffected.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Risk Mitigation & Validation[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate with AddressSanitizer and libFuzzer to confirm no more [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflows in the `%e` path.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing unit tests for `mg_snprintf`, `mg_vsnprintf`, and floating-point [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatting to ensure no regressions.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The enlarged buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has precedent elsewhere in the code, so [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis change is low-risk.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference Code Context[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - code_range: src/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:312[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m330[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - code_range: src/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:273[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m300[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis strategy fully addresses both the initial overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfirst buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersisting overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39msecond buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m by aligning the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch with the safe [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer sizes used in other floating-point formatting paths.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer stack-buffer-overflow was triggered in the Mongoose HTTP [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibrary’s formatted-output routines when parsing HTTP input under fuzzing. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow occurs in mg_pfn_iobuf_private called from mg_vxprintf, indicating that a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal buffer in fmt.c is too small for certain formatted output paths. A patch was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted in fmt.c at the handling of the ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ floating-point conversion: the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` was enlarged to `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, and the call to `mg_dtoa` was [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated to pass the buffer’s size. After applying this patch, the same [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow remains, pointing to the same frame and same offset in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_vxprintf.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mongoose/test/fuzz.c` leads to an AddressSanitizer crash.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error report shows a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte WRITE at a stack address, identified as a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`SCARINESS: [0m[1;36m46[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprintf.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, invoked via `scpy` in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan reports the overflow offset [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m120[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the stack frame of mg_vxprintf. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTwo local arrays are in that frame:  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * `tmp` at offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  * `tmp371` at [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ← the overflow writes at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, one past the end of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp371`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack frame at fmt.c line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere the overflow is detected[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is part of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgeneric vxprintf logic, not just the ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ case.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow target is `tmp371`, a local buffer used in one of the formatting [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths of mg_vxprintf.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash log consistently shows the same stack layout and overflow offset across[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth initial and patched runs.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerable code is in fmt.c, affecting floating-point formatting and possibly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother conversions that use similarly sized buffers.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified src/fmt.c around line [0m[1;36m315[0m[39m, in the branch handling `c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'E'[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  to  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updated the call  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  to  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, c == [0m[32m'e'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult of Patch  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer re-ran [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and produced the same AddressSanitizer [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash still occurs in mg_pfn_iobuf_private via mg_vxprintf at the same offset[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the mg_vxprintf stack frame.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan report still points to `tmp371` [0m[1;39m([0m[39munused by the attempted patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` buffer in the ‘e’[0m[35m/[0m[39m’E’ branch.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The definition and usage of all local buffers in mg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, including [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe one named `tmp371`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The internal implementation of mg_dtoa, scpy, and the iobuf routines to see how [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutput is buffered and copied into these locals.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Other format-specifier branches in mg_vxprintf, to identify any additional small[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffers that could overflow.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The interaction between width/precision handling and buffer sizing in [0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing run with AddressSanitizer on the Mongoose codebase revealed a [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow in the custom printf implementation. The overflow arises in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when writing to a small stack‐allocated buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“tmp371”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was attempted that enlarges one temporary buffer from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m bytes in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'%e'[0m[35m/[0m[32m'%E'[0m[39m branch and replaces a custom exponent formatter with snprintf. After [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer, the same overflow is still reported at the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame stack location, indicating that the patch did not address all vulnerable [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer usages.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer crash log shows AddressSanitizer detecting a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write past the end[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof a stack buffer during a call to mg_pfn_iobuf_private [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprintf.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, invoked from [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscpy in fmt.c.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call stack is roughly:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → mg_http_parse → mg_log → mg_vxprintf → scpy → [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmg_putchar_iobuf_static → mg_pfn_iobuf_private.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASAN pinpoints the overflow at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m in the mg_vxprintf stack frame, within [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man object labeled ‘tmp371’ [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined at fmt.c around line [0m[1;36m319[0m[39m, size [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In src/fmt.c, within the case handling for format specifiers ‘e’ and ‘E’:  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Changed the local buffer declaration from `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` to `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Updated the call to mg_dtoa to pass `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of a fixed [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoid overrunning that buffer.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Replaced the `mg_lld` call used for formatting the exponent with a call to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[32m"%lld"[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After applying these changes, rebuilding, and rerunning the fuzz target, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer still reports the same stack-buffer-overflow in mg_vxprintf at the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame offset and within the same frame.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow remains in the unpatched local buffer object ‘tmp371’ [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich the patch did not modify.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFurther investigation areas  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The full implementation of mg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, especially all uses of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-allocated buffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ‘tmp’ at lines ~[0m[1;36m276[0m[39m and ‘tmp371’ at ~[0m[1;36m319[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Other format-specifier branches in mg_vxprintf [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuch as [0m[32m'%f'[0m[39m, [0m[32m'%g'[0m[39m or integer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformats[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that may rely on small fixed-size buffers.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The behavior and buffer requirements of mg_dtoa and whether its output can exceed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massumed limits.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The scpy function’s loop logic and whether it respects the length parameters [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed to it.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall interaction between fmt.c formatting routines and printf.c I/O buffering [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure all writes stay within allocated memory.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
