[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/fmt.[0m[1;92mc:229[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m234[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m229[0m[39m:static size_t [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid [0m[1;39m([0m[39m*out[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar, void *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, void *ptr, char *buf,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m230[0m[39m:                          size_t len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m231[0m[39m:  size_t i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:  while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi < len && buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, ptr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:  return i;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The AddressSanitizer log consistently points at the small stack‐allocated buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tmp371` in the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch of `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c around line [0m[1;36m319[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  That [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer was declared as [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, yet two formatting calls write more[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes into it:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can produce up to [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m+ bytes.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The exponent formatter [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_lld` or even `[0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"%lld"[0m[39m,…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can exceed [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes when it writes the sign and up to three digits of exponent plus a NUL [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mterminator.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The previous patch correctly changed those calls to respect the buffer size [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mpassing `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to `mg_dtoa` and using `snprintf` for the exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but it [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailed to enlarge the buffer itself in the compiled code. ASan still sees an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer because the modification was either not applied in the correct code path or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch target line numbers drifted.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must not alter how the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` formatting algorithm computes mantissa or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent, nor change the output sequence [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mantissa`, `e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`E`, exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must preserve all corner‐case behaviors of `mg_dtoa` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprecision handling, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrounding, `capitalswitch`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and of the exponent formatting.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We keep using `scpy` to emit characters out via the `out` callback, preserving[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe existing I/O buffering logic in printf.c.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Fix Steps  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/fmt.c`, locate the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch inside `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m in the initial code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Change the small `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` declaration to a larger buffer—ideally [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching the “generic numeric” branch’s [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes, for uniformity and safety:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* before: *[0m[35m/[0m[39m  char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* after:  *[0m[35m/[0m[39m  char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Modify both formatting calls to use the true buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Call `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, mantissa, precision, isExponential[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace any `[0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` usage with a bounds‐checked [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`snprintf`:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        k = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[32m"%+lld"[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptionally[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m clamp `k` to `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` to guard against any library [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moddities, though `snprintf` already does so.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Rebuild and rerun the fuzzer to ensure the stack‐buffer‐overflow is resolved.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mConfirm via AddressSanitizer logs that:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - The overflow no longer occurs in the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - No new buffer overflows emerge in other branches.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Increasing the buffer to [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes matches the existing safe pattern used for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`%f`, `%g`, integer, and pointer formatting elsewhere in `mg_vxprintf`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Passing `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` into `mg_dtoa` enforces that the mantissa formatting [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever writes past the end of the buffer.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `[0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for the exponent eliminates the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbounded write risk of `mg_lld`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These changes leave the overall formatting logic, I/O buffering, and test [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness untouched.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Runtime overhead: Moving from an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte to [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m‐byte stack allocation is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnegligible.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Behavioral change: The only functional change is correct truncation/prevention[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof overruns—actual formatted output is identical to before for all finite exponents[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand mantissas.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Regression risk: Running the existing test suite [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding the fuzz target[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill catch any unintended changes in formatting behavior.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References to Similar Code  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The “generic numeric” branch at lines [0m[1;36m271[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m300[0m[39m in `fmt.c` already uses `char [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with `[0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` safely.  Reusing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat pattern for `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` ensures consistency.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Changes to Harness or External Code  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This patch only touches `src/fmt.c` and does not modify:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any fuzzing harness, test code, or external libraries.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of I/O buffering in `printf.c`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   It fully preserves existing tests and fuzzing entry points. [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpn71ttnsm[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer‐detected stack‐buffer‐overflow occurs in mongoose’s printf/fmt [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic when fuzzing HTTP parsing. The overflow is reported in `mg_pfn_iobuf_private`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39min printf.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, called from `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min fmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where a one‐byte write [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverruns a stack buffer named `tmp371`. [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA proposed patch enlarged one local buffer from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m bytes and switched exponent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatting to `snprintf`, updating:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` → `char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` → `k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `k = [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` → `k = [0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[32m"%+lld"[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRe‐running the fuzzer after applying this patch produced the same overflow at the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame location, showing the patch did not eliminate the out‐of‐bounds write in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_vxprintf`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer, targeting `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `test/fuzz.c`, triggers a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack‐buffer‐overflow in the formatting code.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m‐byte write past the end of a stack‐allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer in `mg_vxprintf` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The offending write occurs in `scpy` → [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_putchar_iobuf_static` → `mg_pfn_iobuf_private`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `mg_vxprintf`, two local arrays are allocated:  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `tmp` at offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m72[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `tmp371` at offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m112[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m120[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow write targets offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, one byte past `tmp371`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Important Observations**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens during `%e` or `%E` formatting, where a mantissa and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexponent are printed.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The second buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tmp371`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m used for exponent formatting is sized only [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes and is overrun by certain inputs.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer indicates that the overflow is reproducible under the same [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing harness.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt Details**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/fmt.c`, within the `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E` branch of `mg_vxprintf`:  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Increased the first buffer size from [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` → `char [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Updated the call to `mg_dtoa` to pass the new buffer size.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Replaced `mg_lld`-based exponent conversion with `snprintf`, writing into [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same `tmp` buffer.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Patch diff snippet:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/fmt.c  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/fmt.c  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-315[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m315[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m15[0m[39m @@  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'e'[0m[39m || c == [0m[32m'E'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      char tmp[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            double d = [0m[1;35mva_arg[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*ap, double[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            …  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      k = [0m[1;35mmg_dtoa[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mout[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc, param[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            n++;  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      k = [0m[1;35mmg_lld[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, exponent, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      k = [0m[1;35msnprintf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp, [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[32m"%+lld"[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mexponent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            n += [0m[1;35mscpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mout, param, tmp, k[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Result After Patch**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still triggers the same stack‐buffer‐overflow at the same code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_pfn_iobuf_private via mg_vxprintf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Sanitizer output again shows overflow by one byte at offset [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `tmp371` remains too small or is still being used incorrectly.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The full implementation of `mg_vxprintf` in `src/fmt.c`, especially the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling of all temporary buffers.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All branches that allocate local buffers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot only `%e`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`%E`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for other format[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`%f`, `%g`, integer formats[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure buffer sizes match worst‐case [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutput.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definitions and behaviors of helper routines: `mg_dtoa`, `mg_lld`, `scpy`, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe static I/O buffer functions in `printf.c`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any additional stack allocations or redzones in `mg_vxprintf` that could be [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmis‐sized.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* hi+lo = f - hfsq + s*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhfsq+R[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ~ [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m+f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:     [0m[39mhi = f - hfsq;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:     [0m[39mu.f = hi;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:     [0m[39mu.i &= [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m<<[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:     [0m[39mhi = u.f;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* val_hi+val_lo ~ [0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m+f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + k*[0m[1;35mlog10[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:     [0m[39m * Extra precision in for adding y is not strictly needed[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:     [0m[39m * since there is no very large cancellation near x = [0m[1;35msqrt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:     [0m[39m * x = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m/[0m[1;35msqrt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but we do it anyway since it costs little on CPUs[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:     [0m[39m * with some parallelism and it reduces the error for many args.[0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m211[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_signed && val < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'-'[0m[39m, v = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m-val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m212[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m This loop prints a number in reverse order. I guess this is because we[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m write numbers from right to left: least significant digit comes last.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Maybe because we use Arabic numbers, and Arabs write RTL?[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mis_hex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; v; v >>= [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = letters[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mv & [0m[1;36m15[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:    for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mn = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; v; v [0m[35m/[0m[39m= [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = letters[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mv % [0m[1;36m10[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Reverse a string[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:  for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < n [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[39m:    char t = buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m223[0m[39m:    buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - i - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ms + n - i - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = t;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m225[0m[39m:  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mval == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buf[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mn++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Handle special case[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m226[0m[39m:  return n + s;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m227[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
